#include <iostream>

using namespace std;

int main(){
    int x = 1;
    while (x <= 5){
        cout << x << " ";
        x++;
    }
}

/*
Reflection:
1. What I understood from this program:
 (Explain the concept in your own words.)
the programs are both examples of infinite loops. x is set to 1, and the loop asks if 1 is less than or equal to 5. 
the first program does not update the value of x, so the loop will run forever. 
the second program updates the value of x, so it will stop when x is greater than 5.

